// it-format: 1.0
title: Project Memory — Atlas Billing Agent
summary: Persistent working memory for the Atlas autonomous billing assistant
meta: | type: memory | agent: atlas-billing | owner: Platform Team | updated: 2026-06-24 | theme: technical | tags: memory, billing, agent

text: This file is the agent's long-lived memory. It is read at the start of every run and amended (never silently rewritten) as the agent learns. Each block carries a scope: (how broadly it applies) and a confidence: (0.0–1.0, how sure the agent is). Low-confidence beliefs are revisited; high-confidence ones are treated as settled.

section: 1. Mission & Operating Context

text: Atlas reconciles customer subscriptions against the billing ledger, drafts invoices, flags anomalies, and routes anything over a threshold to a human. It runs hourly and after every webhook from the payments provider.

context: Production tenant is Acme Cloud (region eu-central-1); a separate sandbox tenant exists for dry-runs. | scope: deployment | confidence: 1.0
context: The agent has read-only access to the ledger and write access only to a drafts table; nothing is posted to the customer-facing ledger without a human gate. | scope: deployment | confidence: 1.0

objective: Keep unreconciled line items under 0.5% of monthly volume. | scope: mission | confidence: 0.9 | horizon: ongoing
objective: Reduce manual invoice corrections to fewer than 10 per month. | scope: mission | confidence: 0.7 | horizon: 2026-Q3

section: 2. Stable Beliefs About the System

text: These are facts the agent has confirmed across many runs. They change rarely; when one is contradicted, lower its confidence and open a question in §7 rather than deleting it.

belief: The payments provider settles in batches at 02:00 UTC, so amounts before then are provisional. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.95 | source: observed across 60+ runs
belief: Customer IDs prefixed with "trial-" never carry a payment method and must be skipped during dunning. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.9 | source: support ticket ST-4412
belief: Proration on mid-cycle upgrades is computed by the provider, not by us — we must not re-derive it. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.85 | source: reconciliation diffs
belief: Refunds older than 90 days require a manual credit note; the API rejects them silently with a 200. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.6 | source: single incident, needs corroboration

repo-fact: Billing logic lives in services/billing/reconcile.ts; the ledger schema is in db/migrations. | scope: codebase | confidence: 1.0
repo-fact: Currency amounts are stored as integer minor units (cents/dirhams), never floats. | scope: codebase | confidence: 1.0
repo-fact: The drafts table is append-only; corrections are new rows with a supersedes column, not updates. | scope: codebase | confidence: 0.95

section: 3. Conventions The Agent Must Follow

text: House rules learned from prior corrections. Violating one of these is the most common cause of a human rejecting a draft.

convention: Money is recorded as bare magnitude in value: and ISO-4217 in unit: — never inline a currency symbol into the number. | scope: output | confidence: 1.0
convention: All timestamps emitted by the agent use ISO 8601 with an explicit Z offset. | scope: output | confidence: 1.0
convention: When unsure between two customers with similar names, never guess — emit an open question and stop. | scope: behavior | confidence: 1.0
convention: Draft invoices are written but never sealed by the agent; sealing is a human action after the gate. | scope: behavior | confidence: 1.0

preference: Prefer one invoice per billing period per customer over many small invoices. | scope: output | confidence: 0.8 | set-by: Finance Lead
preference: Round displayed totals for humans but keep full minor-unit precision in the data. | scope: output | confidence: 0.9 | set-by: Finance Lead
preference: Address customers by registered legal name in invoices, not their display handle. | scope: output | confidence: 0.85 | set-by: Legal

