text: Total value currently held in draft, awaiting the human gate, this period. | end: 412,800 QAR

section: 6. Lessons Learned (from corrections)

text: When a human overrides the agent, the why is recorded here so the same mistake is not repeated.

lesson: Do not auto-apply a credit before confirming the original charge actually settled — provisional reversals double-counted twice in May. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.9 | learned: 2026-05-30 | corrected-by: Mariam Haddad
lesson: Trial accounts that later add a card keep the "trial-" prefix; key off the payment-method flag, not the ID prefix, when deciding to bill. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.8 | learned: 2026-06-11
lesson: Multi-currency customers must be reconciled per-currency; mixing them inflated the unreconciled rate by ~4x in one run. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.85 | learned: 2026-06-02

assumption: PayRail batch timing (02:00 UTC) is stable; if a settlement looks late, suspect a provider incident before suspecting our code. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.6 | revisit: 2026-09-01

section: 7. Open Questions

text: Things the agent does not yet know and should resolve before raising its confidence on related beliefs.

openq: Does PayRail expose a webhook for late/retried settlements, or must we poll? | scope: integration | confidence: 0.3 | blocks: belief on refund handling
openq: What is the correct treatment of a partial refund on a multi-line invoice — per-line or whole-invoice? | scope: billing | confidence: 0.4
openq: Is there an SLA on human approval we should encode as an escalation timer? | scope: governance | confidence: 0.5

watch: Refund-older-than-90-days behavior — only seen once; raise confidence on the §2 belief only after a second confirmed case. | scope: billing | confidence: 0.6
watch: Provider API v4 migration announced for Q4 — re-validate all integration beliefs when it lands. | scope: integration | confidence: 0.7 | due: 2026-10-01

section: 8. Standing Decisions

text: Design choices that are settled. Recorded so the agent does not relitigate them every run.

decided: The human gate is mandatory for any single draft over 100,000 QAR — never auto-approve, regardless of confidence. | scope: governance | confidence: 1.0 | by: Finance Lead | at: 2026-05-15
decided: The agent writes memory amendments in append-only fashion; it never edits a sealed prior memory snapshot. | scope: governance | confidence: 1.0 | by: Platform Team | at: 2026-04-02
decided: When two beliefs conflict, the one with the more recent, higher-confidence source wins, and the loser is downgraded — not deleted. | scope: reasoning | confidence: 0.9 | by: Platform Team | at: 2026-04-02

section: 9. Run Checklist

text: The agent walks this ordered list at the start of every run.

1. Reload this memory file and reconcile beliefs against the latest ledger snapshot.
2. Skip any customer flagged trial with no payment method (§3, §6).
3. Reconcile each currency separately (§6 lesson).
4. Draft invoices for the closed period; write to the drafts table only.
5. Route any draft over the threshold to the human gate (§8).
6. Record corrections as new lessons and adjust confidence (§6).

task: Confirm refund-over-90-days behavior with PayRail support | owner: Atlas | due: 2026-07-05 | priority: medium
task: Encode human-approval SLA once §7 question is answered | owner: Platform Team | due: 2026-07-31 | priority: low
done: Migrated draft writes to append-only supersedes model | at: 2026-04-10
done: Added per-currency reconciliation pass | at: 2026-06-03

section: 10. Governance & Sign-off

text: This memory snapshot is reviewed monthly. Sign-offs below are pre-seal approvals; the file is sealed by a human after review (the agent never seals its own memory).

info: This document is intentionally left pre-seal. To lock a reviewed snapshot, a human runs sealDocument() — the agent must not invent a freeze:/hash:. | type: warning

